    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-16T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-16T07:00:00-05:00" n="296"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.51/4060: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-16T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 16, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 16—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>112. Negotiations in progress in Berlin with Dutch and Swiss for special transfer
                    agreements which if obtained will be notified to other creditors. It was
                    indicated at the Foreign Office that Governments of countries mentioned showed
                    willingness to reduce rate of interest and statement attributed to President
                    Roosevelt in <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi> of February 8th last was
                    cited as evidence that American Government viewed reduction of interest on
                    foreign indebtedness as reasonable. Communiqué published intimates that
                    imposition English clearing would be met by countermeasure against whole British
                    Empire but presumed at the Foreign Office that there would be Dawes–Young
                    settlement negotiated with funding bonds or increased export of goods.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodd</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
